    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nFixed-width C integer types are somewhat system / C-compiler specific and thus not entirely trivial to use. However, Cython is not C. They fill a common need and should be easy to use.\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nInstead of requiring cimports from `stdint.h`, Cython should just know about common types like `uint32_t` etc.\r\nThese need to be added to both `PyrexTypes.py` (plain C types) and `Shadow.py` (`cython.*`).\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\nOriginally proposed in https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4980#issuecomment-1217554257",
